http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 11 Jul 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(28) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=24232


Foot and mouth disease, Congo (Dem. Rep. of the)
------------------------------------------------
Information received on 11 Jul 2017 from Mr Honore Robert N'Lemba Mabela, [Director and Head of Service, Animal Health and Production Service, Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Livestock, Kinshasa], Congo (Dem. Rep. of the)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 May 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 6 Jul 2017
Report date: 7 Jul 2017
Date submitted to OIE: 11 Jul 2017
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: not typed
Nature of diagnosis: clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (4)
Outbreak 1: Bijombo centre, Uvira, Sud-Kivu
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4326 / 282 / 17 / 0 / 9

Outbreak 2: Masango, Uvira, Sud-Kivu
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2213 / 161 / 6 / 0 / 6

Outbreak 3: Rubarati, Uvira, Sud-Kivu
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1322 / 128 / 4 / 0 / 2

Outbreak 4: Muramvya, Uvira, Sud-Kivu
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2318 / 245 / 9 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 4
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 10 179 / 816 / 36 / 0 / 17
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 8.02 / 0.35 / 4.41 / 0.52
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: introduction of new live animals, Illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: the heads of cattle hit by the disease are of all ages and of all sexes. Young and animals from improved breeds are the most affected. Note from the World Animal Health Information and Analysis Department: the disease is present in the province of Sud-Kivu but it is a 1st occurrence on the territory of Uvira.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, quarantine;, zoning, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), treatment of affected animals (737 cases treated; disinfection of the wounds with denaturated alcohol.)
Measures to be applied: surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As is noted by the World Animal Health Information and Analysis Department, FMD is present in the province of Sud-Kivu, however, this is the 1st occurrence of the disease in the territory of Uvira.

According to the most recent information available in the OIE WAHIS database, the Democratic Republic of the Congo reported during the 2nd half of 2016, 16 outbreaks of FMD. The serotypes identified were A, O, and SAT 1. The outbreaks were located in the provinces of Haut-Lomani (2), Ituri (2), Nord-Kivu (4), Sud-Kivu (4), and Tanganika (2). See report and details of the outbreaks at http://tinyurl.com/ycwq8d8s. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5182104,51976.]
